NAME

odgi â€” utilities for manipulating GFA

handle - refers to oriented nodes;
path_handle - the path handle type, which refers to paths;
step_handle - the step handle type, which refers to path paths;
edge - edges link two handles together.

./odgi <command> [options]

--build.. convert gfa in odgi i.e. variation graph

Options:

-g, GFA input file
-o, ODGI output file 

LIST OF COMMANDS

import odgi

###1. <g> = odgi.graph()  
Define graph

##2. <g>.load("file")  
Load file in graph

##3. <g>.append_step(options)
Append a visit to a node to the given path. Returns a handle to the new final step on the path which is appended.

-odgi.graph - default
-g.path_handle
-g.handle - look handle
   
 ##4. <g>.get_handle(options)
Return the handle for the given node id

-odgi.graph SELF 
-node_id INT- mandatory
-is_reverse BOOL - not obligatory
False(+) or True(-) based on the orientation of the DNA

##5. <g>.get_id(options) 
Return id of given handle

-odgi.graph - already defined
-handle - Look g.get_handle

##6. <g>.to_gfa()
Display as GFA

-without parameters

##-g.get_sequence(options)
Return sequence of given handle

-odgi.graph SELF
-handle
